<p>I now that the function count can be used to count the number of elements in a given sequence, like this:</p>  <pre><code>count(result/actors/actor) </code></pre>  <p>in this XML:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;result&gt;     &lt;actors&gt;         &lt;actor id="00000015"&gt;Anderson, Jeff&lt;/actor&gt;         &lt;actor id="00000030"&gt;Bishop, Kevin&lt;/actor&gt;         &lt;actor id="0000000f"&gt;Bonet, Lisa&lt;/actor&gt;         &lt;actor id="916503207"&gt;Parillaud, Anne&lt;/actor&gt;         &lt;actor id="916503208"&gt;Pitt, Brad&lt;/actor&gt;         &lt;actor id="916503209"&gt;Freeman, Morgan&lt;/actor&gt;         &lt;actor id="916503211"&gt;Domingo, Placido&lt;/actor&gt;         &lt;actor id="916503210"&gt;Sharif, Omar&lt;/actor&gt;         &lt;actor id="1337"&gt;Doqumenteriet2011&lt;/actor&gt;     &lt;/actors&gt; &lt;/result&gt; </code></pre>  <p>But what if I want to know how many times a value occurs in a given sequence?</p>  <p>For example if I would like to know how many movies each actor (actorRef) appeared in in the following XML:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;videos&gt;     &lt;video id="id1235AA0"&gt;         &lt;title&gt;The Fugitive&lt;/title&gt;         &lt;actorRef&gt;00000003&lt;/actorRef&gt;         &lt;actorRef&gt;00000006&lt;/actorRef&gt;     &lt;/video&gt;     &lt;video id="id1244100"&gt;         &lt;title&gt;Enemy of the State&lt;/title&gt;         &lt;actorRef&gt;00000009&lt;/actorRef&gt;         &lt;actorRef&gt;0000000c&lt;/actorRef&gt;         &lt;actorRef&gt;0000000f&lt;/actorRef&gt;         &lt;actorRef&gt;00000012&lt;/actorRef&gt;     &lt;/video&gt;     &lt;video id="id124E230"&gt;         &lt;title&gt;Clerks&lt;/title&gt;         &lt;actorRef&gt;00000015&lt;/actorRef&gt;         &lt;actorRef&gt;00000018&lt;/actorRef&gt;         &lt;actorRef&gt;0000001b&lt;/actorRef&gt;     &lt;/video&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I can easily produce a list of all the appearing actors, and even have them appear as many times in my produced sequence as in the XML:</p>  <pre><code>result/videos//actorRef </code></pre>  <p>but I am not able to do anything similar to what for example COUNT() and GROUP BY do together in SQL to get a list of the actors by count of their multiplicity in the sequence produced by the above line of XQuery.</p>  <p>How can I produce this list?</p>  <p>PS: The end goal is to find the actors that appeared the most movies.</p>